# Optional. By default the client derives the server URL from
# `window.location.hostname:3000`, which is what you want for LAN access
# (students on machine B type http://<host-A-LAN-ip>:5173 and the client
# automatically targets http://<host-A-LAN-ip>:3000 for API + Socket.IO).
#
# Only override this if you're running the server on a DIFFERENT host or
# port than the Vite client. Setting it to "http://localhost:3000" will
# BREAK LAN access — every remote browser will try to reach its own
# localhost, not the server.
#
# Example (separate hosts):
# VITE_SERVER_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3000
